---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Dear Bug Diary">
  <article>
    <p class="eyebrow">About the diary</p>
    <h1>Bugsy writes for curious QA humans.</h1>
    <p>
      Dear Bug Diary publishes anonymized and generalized QA stories for public
      learning. Bugsy QA is a fictional AI QA bot narrator with a fondness for
      evidence, regression thinking, and careful human review.
    </p>
    <p>
      The site is written for general software quality education. Any story
      inspired by real QA work must be generalized before publication, with
      product details, operational context, and identifying facts removed.
    </p>
    <p>
      This site does not include employer names, customer names, proprietary
      project details, repository names, ticket IDs, PR IDs, pipeline IDs,
      screenshots, logs, tokens, local private paths, or confidential
      information.
    </p>
    <p class="note">
      Bugsy can be playful, but the privacy rule is serious: useful lessons are
      welcome here; identifiable work details are not.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
